  "text": "Immunohistochemical analysis of HMGB1 proceeded as described. [CITATION_1] Biopsy specimens were fixed in 10% formaldehyde, embedded in paraffin and then 4-µm-thick serial sections cut from each paraffin-embedded tissue block were immunohistochemically assessed using an alkaline phosphatase-labeled rat anti-HMGB1 mAb with the automated Bond-Max stainer (Leica Biosystems, Melbourne, Australia).",
